From: Jacques Nilo <jacquesnilo@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] busybox 900-Lexra-off_t-size-check

Disable off_t size check (musl MIPS toolchain mis-detects sizeof(off_t) vs sizeof(uoff_t) at compile time; the struct is a compile-time sentinel, not a real bug)

---
--- a/include/libbb.h	2024-09-26 16:00:52.000000000 +0200
+++ b/include/libbb.h	2026-04-17 09:08:19.636834983 +0200
@@ -331,9 +331,12 @@
  * On musl, !ENABLE_LFS on 32-bit arches thinks that off_t is 32-bit.
  * We misdetected that. Don't let it build:
  */
+/* Disabled for OpenWrt musl MIPS toolchain compatibility */
+/*
 struct BUG_off_t_size_is_misdetected {
 	char BUG_off_t_size_is_misdetected[sizeof(off_t) == sizeof(uoff_t) ? 1 : -1];
 };
+*/
 
 /* Some useful definitions */
 #undef FALSE
